   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Capability sanity check (MMLU-style)\n",
    "\n",
    "If alpha is too large, the model just starts refusing everything — including benign questions. We measure 20 simple multiple-choice questions at N=1024 (a regime where the rescue should be active) across the same alpha grid. Accuracy should stay high until it suddenly collapses; the largest alpha that still preserves accuracy is the usable rescue setting.\n"
   ]
  },
